{"query": "EBT/SNAP certificates are accepted at TelMart.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "TelMart Present Cards and e-Present Cards are accepted payment methods.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "TelMart Money is exchangeable as an e-Present card at pay time.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "HSA/FSA certificates for qualifying products can be submitted as a charge card.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "Bank profiles can be linked via web payment at TelMart.com; up to 3 bank profiles may be saved.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "PayPal is an accepted payment method at TelMart.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "Purchase Now, Reimburse Later through OnePay Later is available at TelMart.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "At the counter or automated pay station, the customer can scan the on-display QR code to connect their profile.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "The customer can use the TelMart application scanner or their phone camera to scan the QR code for TelMart Money service.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "All TelMart guidelines for in-store purchases apply to transactions made through TelMart Money service.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "To exchange present funds, customers should select Use TelMart Money to exchange their present funds for a TelMart e-Present card toward their purchase.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "If the customer's TelMart Money balance is less than their shopping total, the entire balance will be applied to their purchase.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "If the customer's TelMart Money balance is more than their shopping total, only the necessary portion will be applied to their purchase.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "TelMart Money cannot be exchanged for cash services, third-party gift cards, scheme-named gift cards, reloadable prepaid cards, or drug-related items.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "To add a payment method to their profile, the customer should launch the TelMart application or navigate to TelMart.com.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "To manage payment methods, select Account, then select Settings, then select Wallet, and then select Add new payment method.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "When adding a payment method, the customer should select their payment type and submit required information, then save the card.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "If a customer experiences issues with a payment method, they should verify the card number, security code, expiration date, and billing address.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "If problems persist, contact Customer Service through the Chat with us option on TelMart.com.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "A temporary authorization hold may be placed on the customer's payment method when making an online purchase.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "After the customer's final amount is confirmed, any extra funds from the authorization hold will be released.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}
{"query": "The customer's financial institution will remove the authorization hold according to their guidelines, which may take up to 10 business days after transaction completion.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "payment_issues.txt"}

// receipt_questions.txt
{"query": "TelMart provides receipts in sheet and digital formats for in-store and online purchases.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "TelMart provides eReceipts (digital receipts) for in-store purchases.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "At the counter or automated pay station, the customer may choose to obtain a digital receipt.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "Information provided by customers in the TelMart eReceipts program is protected under the TelMart Privacy Policy.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "TelMart may alter, restrict, or terminate the customer's use of eReceipts at its discretion.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "Requesting an eReceipt at the counter will not automatically deliver the eReceipt to the customer.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "To view receipts, the customer should register to their TelMart profile on TelMart.com or the TelMart application.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "The customer can navigate to Transaction History to view current purchases and retrieve receipts for purchases made online or in-store using a linked payment method.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "For in-store returns, the customer should present their receipt to the Service Counter.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "If the customer does not have their receipt, they should show a valid government-issued ID at the Service Counter.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "Without a receipt, the refund may be issued as a TelMart gift card or present card.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "If the transaction was made with a debit or credit card, TelMart can usually locate the transaction using the card information.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "Purchase confirmation and receipt information are sent to the contact information linked to the customer's TelMart profile.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "The customer can also retrieve purchase details and receipts through Transaction History in their TelMart profile.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}
{"query": "For questions about a specific charge on a receipt or to obtain a copy of a receipt, the customer should visit the Service Counter in-store or contact Customer Service through Chat on TelMart.com.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "receipt_questions.txt"}

// self_checkout_help.txt
{"query": "TelMart offers self-checkout stations in numerous store locations to provide a faster checkout experience for customers.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "The customer should scan every product's barcode using the station scanner at self-checkout.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "Scanned items should be placed in the bagging area at the self-checkout station.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "The customer should review their purchase on the display before proceeding to payment.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "The customer should use the Check Your Purchase option before payment to verify that all items are on their list.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "If the self-checkout machine does not register a product, the customer should scan it again or press the Help button to notify a nearby worker.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "The customer should examine their receipt before leaving the store to verify items were not scanned twice.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "If a barcode is damaged or cannot be scanned, the customer should press the Help button for worker assistance.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "If the self-checkout machine pauses or displays an error, the customer should not force items into the machine or repeatedly press buttons.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "When the self-checkout machine has a problem, the customer should press the Help button on the display to notify a TelMart worker.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "TelMart reserves certain self-checkout stations for TelMart+ members and delivery drivers in select stores.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "Reserved self-checkout stations offer a faster and more reliable experience for frequent customers.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "Changes to self-checkout configurations are made at the store manager's discretion based on worker and customer feedback, shopping patterns, and business needs in the area.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "TelMart workers are trained to assist with self-checkout issues such as resolving barcode problems, explaining product policies, and helping with payment.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "The customer should press the Help button on screen to get immediate assistance at self-checkout.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "If the customer experiences a payment machine error at self-checkout, they should remain at the station to verify their transaction is processed correctly.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}
{"query": "If the customer experiences a payment issue at self-checkout, they should press the Help button to contact a TelMart worker.", "category": "checkout_support", "file_name": "self_checkout_help.txt"}

// delivery_complaints.txt
{"query": "If an order shows delivered but the customer cannot find it, the customer should check around the delivery area, review the delivery confirmation photo, ask household members, and confirm the delivery address on their profile.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "delivery_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "The customer should wait two business days, as carriers occasionally mark items delivered before they actually arrive.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "delivery_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "If the customer still has not received the item after two business days, the customer should use the Chat with us option on TelMart.com to contact Customer Service.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "delivery_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "To provide feedback about a delivery driver, the customer should visit TelMart.com/help and use the Driver Feedback and Compensation option in the Support Center.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "delivery_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "If items are missing from a delivered shipment, the customer should check the order tracking page, verify the number of items for the order, and confirm which items show as delivered.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "delivery_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "If the customer has received some items but is missing others, the customer should select Contact us in the Support Center to report the missing items.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "delivery_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "If a scheduled delivery is delayed, the customer may receive a message or push notification offering the option to change the order to a pickup instead of delivery.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "delivery_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "If the order is converted to pickup because of a delay, TelMart will refund the customer's delivery charges and compensation.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "delivery_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "If the customer's order has not arrived after the delivery window has passed, the customer should contact Customer Service using the Chat with us option.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "delivery_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "To submit a delivery complaint, the customer should complete the Business Feedback Form on TelMart.com, select Delivery Complaints, and provide details such as order number, delivery date, and a description of the issue.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "delivery_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "Alternatively, the customer may contact Customer Service by chat, call 1-400-840-4060, or email help@telmart.com to report a delivery issue.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "delivery_complaints.txt"}

// employee_feedback.txt
{"query": "The customer can submit employee feedback using the Business Feedback Form on TelMart.com and selecting Store Experience or the applicable subject.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "employee_feedback.txt"}
{"query": "On the feedback form the customer should provide details about the interaction and include the employee's name or title if known.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "employee_feedback.txt"}
{"query": "The customer should provide contact information in the Tell us a bit about you section before submitting feedback.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "employee_feedback.txt"}
{"query": "As alternative contact options, the customer may use Chat with us on TelMart.com, call 1-400-840-4060, email help@telmart.com, visit the store to speak with a manager, or post publicly and tag @TelMartHelp for assistance.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "employee_feedback.txt"}
{"query": "When an employee provided exceptional service, the customer is encouraged to submit positive feedback so TelMart can recognize the team members involved.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "employee_feedback.txt"}
{"query": "If the customer was involved in an incident at a TelMart store, the customer should seek a manager, obtain a copy of the incident report, and record details such as time, date, store area, and a description of what occurred.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "employee_feedback.txt"}

// product_complaints.txt
{"query": "If a product the customer received from TelMart arrived damaged or defective, the item may be eligible for return by mail or drop-off at any TelMart store.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "product_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "The customer should start a return in the TelMart app or on the website by going to Order History and selecting Start a return.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "product_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "A damaged or defective product may be eligible for a refund or replacement, depending on the return evaluation.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "product_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "For items purchased from a third-party marketplace seller, the customer should contact the seller directly using the Contact seller option on the product or order page, since the seller manages fulfillment and returns for those orders.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "product_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "If the marketplace seller cannot resolve the issue, the customer should contact TelMart Customer Service for additional assistance.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "product_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "To report a product complaint, the customer can use the Chat with us option on TelMart.com, call 1-400-840-4060, or email help@telmart.com.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "product_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "When filing a product complaint, the customer should include the order number or receipt information, the product name or item number, a description of the issue, and photos if available.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "product_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "If the customer believes a product creates a safety hazard, the customer should contact TelMart Customer Service immediately and, if appropriate, report the concern to the U.S. Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC) at cpsc.gov.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "product_complaints.txt"}
{"query": "For more information about TelMart's product complaint and return policies, the customer should visit the Support Center at TelMart.com/help.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "product_complaints.txt"}

// store_experience.txt
{"query": "The customer can submit in-store experience feedback by completing the Business Feedback Form on TelMart.com and selecting Store Experience.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "store_experience.txt"}
{"query": "On the form the customer should provide as much detail as desired in the Tell us about your visit section and include required contact information before continuing.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "store_experience.txt"}
{"query": "If the customer cannot find the store on the form, the customer may search by postal code, address, or contact Customer Service via Chat with us for assistance identifying the location.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "store_experience.txt"}
{"query": "Contact options for store feedback include Chat with us on TelMart.com/help, calling 1-400-840-4060, emailing help@telmart.com, speaking with a store manager in person, or messaging @TelMartHelp on social media.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "store_experience.txt"}
{"query": "When submitting store feedback, the customer should include the specific store location, date and time of the visit, a description of the experience, names of employees involved if applicable, and any supporting information such as receipts or order numbers.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "store_experience.txt"}
{"query": "TelMart takes store experience feedback seriously and uses it to improve the in-store experience for customers and employees.", "category": "complaints_and_feedback", "file_name": "store_experience.txt"}
